Title: ATLAS BELITTLED BY SOVIET VISITOR: WOMAN ASTROPHYSICIST CALLS TALKING SATELLITE SMALL AND NOTHING NEW
Abstract: A Russian astrophysicist said here yesterday that the Atlas satellite launched last week should really be compared with the first and smallest Sputnik.

Title: DOCK MEN AGREE ON LABOR SAVER: I.L.A. AND EMPLOYERS REACH YEAR'S PACT TO ALLOW USE OF SOME CONTAINERS
Abstract: Longshoremen and employers on the New York waterfront reached a temporary agreement yesterday in the controversy over using huge containers for handling ocean freight.

Title: ELECTRIC EYE ERA: SYSTEMS OF AUTOMATIC LENS APERTURE SETTINGS EASE LIFE OF PHOTOGRAPHER
Abstract: ONCE merely a photographic light measuring device and exposure calculator (which essentially it still is, of course), the photoelectric cell has assumed within the last year or two the status of symbol, the rallying point for a host of new devices designed to promote automation and simplification in amateur picture-taking.
